  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to investigate whether positron emission tomography (PET) using the
      tracer 18F-Fluorothymidine (FLT) can provide information on proliferative activity in bone
      marrow of patients receiving Radium 223 therapy and potentially be a predictive marker of
      hematological toxicity
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
